   plugin allows hiding specific columns from the table. (Note, that these columns are still being rendered - the plugin
      just hides them using CSS).
  </p>
  <h3 id="setup">
   content8
  </h3>
  <p>
   The
   <code>
    content9
   </code>
   parameter accepts an object. To provide the columns to hide, you need to specify the
   <code>
    content10
   </code>
   property for the object -
      it should be defined as an array of numbers, which represent the indexes of columns that need to be hidden.
   <br/>
   <br/>
